{"article_id":"2XRwimi2x3bEriMY","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"KIEV , Ukraine -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Central Kiev was calm Sunday morning","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"as protesters milled about ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"cleaning ,","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"congratulating","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"and shaking their heads in wonderment over the dizzying events of the past day ,","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"when Ukraine 's president was forced to flee ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"his rival was freed","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"and a revolution was won .","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"But the overarching sentiment in Independence Square and in many other parts of the country was justice- namely in regard to President Viktor Yanukovych ,","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"who was ousted by parliament Saturday .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"Lawmakers selected parliament speaker Oleksandr Turchinov to become interim president Sunday .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"`` Yanukovych must be prosecuted for his crimes ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"and now I have no doubts","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"that he will be , ''","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"said Olena Boyko , 49 , a protester from Kiev .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"`` But we should n't forget about all of his allies ;","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"they must face the courtroom all together , the whole gang .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"`` It 's too early to speak of a victory","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"till this happens , ''","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"she said .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"Sunday , it was unclear where Yanukovych was .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"The State Border Service told Ukrainian media","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"that his plane was stopped over a problem with paperwork at Donetsk city airport Saturday","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"before the aircraft departed the country .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"A day earlier , Yanukovych had defiantly stated","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"he had no intention of leaving office .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"`` I wo n't leave the country ,","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"and I wo n't resign","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"- I am the legitimately elected leader , ''","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"he said in a televised statement ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"calling the events Saturday a `` coup . ''","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"`` I think","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"if Yanukovych does n't find asylum in a third-world country ,","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"he will soon be arrested for an attempt","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"to drag the army into a war against civilians , ''","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"said Taras Berezovets , head of Berta Communications in Kiev .","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"If the mood at his residence , Mezhyhyria , was anything to go by ,","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"he could be punished for more than that .","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"On the outskirts of the city , thousands milled around the palace Sunday","depth":5},{"id":41,"text":"after it was taken over by protesters a day earlier .","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"Inside the luxurious residence , visitors were shocked at the excess","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"- including Italian marble and chandeliers .","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"The president ,","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"whose salary is officially about $ 100,000 annually ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"could never have afforded such luxury ,","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"they said .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"`` I wanted to see with my own eyes","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"that the splendor","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"we see here","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"has n't been conjured or imagined , ''","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"Serhiy Rybakov , a construction worker in the capital told Kyiv Post .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"`` I was n't simply in wonderment ,","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"I was in awe of what I saw in all its pomposity .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"I do n't think","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"many would want to live in these conditions","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"when it 's built on other people 's blood , on other people 's money . ''","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Protesters spoke of justice for the dozens","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"that died last week in the violence after the government 's attempt","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"to shut down the protests .","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"Many wondered what is next for the country .","depth":5},{"id":62,"text":"Turchinov will govern until elections :","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"Saturday , parliament moved up elections to May 25 from the December date","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"that was part of a deal","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"brokered between the president and the opposition Friday","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"to stop the violence .","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"Lawmakers will consider banning the president from running in upcoming elections.","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"Sunday , lawmakers moved to select other ministers","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"after scores from Yanukovych 's Party of Regions resigned Saturday .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"Imprisoned opposition leader and former prime minister Yulia Tymoshenko was released Saturday","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"after spending 21⁄2 years in prison .","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"Hours after her release , Tymoshenko , 53 , spoke to a crowd","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"gathered at Independence Square .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"`` A dictator is gone ,","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"and you are the heroes .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"You are the best of Ukraine , ''","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"she told the crowd of thousands .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"`` But you may not leave here","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"until you finish the job","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"and we go all the way . ''","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"Protesters said","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"they have no intention of leaving the square","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"until they see real change .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"Sunday , masked protesters kept guard over barricades","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"surrounding the square and the husk of the smoking Trade Union House ,","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"which was burned during last week 's violence .","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"`` We need to make strict demands for programs","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"and force the new leaders","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"elected","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"( in May elections )","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"to fulfill them , ''","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"said Oleg Snigur ,","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"who has been on the main square in the Ukrainian capital","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"since protests started in late November .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"`` We do n't care about the names","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"( of the incoming leaders )","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"- what we care about is actions , ''","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"listing his top priorities of police reform , the fight against corruption and a trade agreement with the European Union .","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"The president 's rejection of that treaty triggered Ukraine 's months of political unrest and its second revolution in 10 years .","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"Analysts say","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"they expect a temporary government to be installed until elections .","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"`` Turchinov will offer candidates for prime minister and the rest of the government","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"- this will be a technical government","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"and operate for three months before the","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"( presidential )","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"elections , ''","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"Berezovets said .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"`` Tymoshenko will run for president , ''","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"`` But she may not win","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"- but in that case , she would likely be the prime minister . '' `` She said the right things , ''","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"said protester Vasyl Klimenko , 29 , in Kiev .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"`` I agree with most of it .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"I think","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"she could be","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"( a good )","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"president . ''","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":237,"left":0,"right":236,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":236,"left":175,"right":235,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":175,"left":157,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":138,"right":156,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":138,"left":129,"right":137,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":126,"right":128,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":126,"left":1,"right":125,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":2,"right":124,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":121,"right":123,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":121,"left":3,"right":120,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":120,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":123,"left":6,"right":122,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":122,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":128,"left":127,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":134,"right":136,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":134,"left":132,"right":133,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":132,"left":131,"right":15,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":12,"right":130,"relation":"restatement","nucleari